      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FERAGO (3) made a mess of promising hurdler Zinovation last week at Warrnambool, winning by 15 lengths, which could have been a lot greater if the jockey wanted. Has an obvious aptitude for the jumping caper and the only question mark is whether he backs up, but he's done that with success on the flat before. GOLDEN CRUSADER (4) has always had a bit of a rap on him as a jumper and his recent form is a lot better than all others bar FERAGO, so he looks the main danger. POINT NEPEAN (1) is the best-performed jumper in the race, but his best form appears in previous preparations. Has had a steeplechase run this time in, though, albeit beaten almost 12 lengths when fifth two back. Did win a chasing trial on June 15, though, so might be ready to run an improved race. HULA BEAT (5) making up the numbers.",
